  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cyclone Mora Emergency Food Response in Cox&#x2019;s Bazar</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is distributing food rations of rice, lentils, sugar, and oil to 5,600 households affected by Cyclone Mora.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;	Tropical Cyclone Mora made landfall in the coastal region of Bangladesh on May 30, 2017 at around 6 am. 
&#x2022;	The heavy rains and strong winds affected over 2.8 million people living across the 12 high-risk coastal districts. 
&#x2022;	With an estimated maximum wind speed of 117 kph the cyclone resulted in strong winds and heavy rainfall with storm surge flooding. As early as May 29th, a pre-emptive measure was conducted in the affected areas in the southern coast with nearly 500,000 people evacuated.</narrative>
  </description>
